King of the mountain:  Who can hold a designated peak in Frontier Mountains?<br>
Icy Fingers:  In IC, two groups stand on opposing ends of one of those ice floe paths that connect the bigger islands, and the two forces charge each other.<br>
Crushbone: One group takes over the castle, the other has to try and take it from them.<br>
Maiden's Voyage:  Two groups board the boat in FP and position themselves at different ends of the boat, and once everyone has zoned into OOT the battle begins.  Whoever makes it to BB wins.  (Melee only, as casting can't be performed on a boat... I'm hoping pvp melee can.)<br>
Spirocs: Race to the top of the roost and hold it. <br>
Velks:  A battle on the icy floor above the drop into the pit.  People are bound to slide into the hole (Yark at least)<br>
And some other potential battle grounds: Kerra Island, Paludal Caverns, Sol A, Blackburrow, etc.<br>
<br>
I think this would be a fun break because it seems like many of us have fallen into the trap of thinking that EVERY minute we're logged on EQ has to be spent bettering our characters, regardless of whether it is actually fun.  After grinding to 60, I personally need something that focuses on the fun of EQ rather than the character building aspect.<br>
<br>
But I do agree that if people request to not participate then we should leave them out of it.  I just hope enough people are interested to make this worthwhile.<br>
<br>
I'd be interested in hearing other's take on this.  Jedc, Lash, et al. <p>Mezick <br>
60 Enchanter<br>
